.TH ZENV 1 "2026-05-18" "zenv 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zenv \- personal shell environment toolkit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zenv
.I command
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B zenv
manages persistent shell variables, named "modes" of aliases/functions/env,
and cwd persistence across terminal sessions. Mutating subcommands emit
shell code on stdout; install the shell hook with
.B eval "$(zenv shell-init zsh)"
in your rc.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B shell-init \fIshell\fR
Print shell glue. Supported shells: zsh.
.TP
.B var set \fIname\fR \fIvalue\fR
Persist a variable and emit its export.
.TP
.B var get \fIname\fR
Print a variable's value.
.TP
.B var unset \fIname\fR
Remove a persistent variable; emit unset.
.TP
.B var ls
List persistent variables.
.TP
.B version
Print version.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/zenv/
Mode definitions.
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/zenv/
Per-host state (vars, active modes, cwd history).
